-- Egypt's pound stable on official and black markets
-- By Stephen Kalin
-- Wed Jun 18, 2014 07:49AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 18 (Reuters) - The Egyptian pound was unchanged at a central bank dollar sale on Wednesday and steady on the black market.

The central bank said it sold $37.6 million at a cut-off price of 7.1401 pounds <CBEO> on Wednesday, unchanged from the previous sale on Monday. It had offered $40 million. The dollar was offered for 7.39 pounds in the black market on Wednesday, the same as Monday's rate, according to a black market trader.